* ============================================================
*  TABLE-BUFFER WAL — PHASE B RECOVERY SETUP (leaves an uncommitted .tbj)
*
*  Status:  CANDIDATE / REVIEW_BEFORE_EXECUTION. MUTATING (throwaway table).
*  Purpose: Build WALREC with recno 1 NAME="Original", enable persistent
*           buffering, buffer a REPLACE to "Recovered", and END WITHOUT COMMIT.
*           That leaves a .tbj redo log with a U record and NO commit marker
*           (an uncommitted transaction) and the DBF still holding "Original".
*           The runner then appends a "C" marker (simulating a crash after the
*           commit was durably logged but before the DBF was updated) and reopens.
*
*  RUN (host, via the Phase B runner):
*    powershell -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File .\dottalkpp\data\scripts\pinocchio\run_wal_phaseB_proof_teed.ps1
* ============================================================
SET ECHO OFF
SET TIMER ON
SET TALK ON

SET PATH DBF DBF/pinocchio

* fresh throwaway table
CLOSE
ERASE TABLE WALREC CONFIRM
CREATE X64 WALREC (ID N(4), NAME C(20))
APPEND
REPLACE ID WITH "1"
REPLACE NAME WITH "Original"
COUNT
GO 1
ECHO --- baseline on disk: recno 1 NAME = Original ---
DISPLAY

ECHO --- enable persistent buffer; buffered REPLACE writes an UNCOMMITTED .tbj ---
TABLE BUFFER ON PERSISTENT
GO 1
REPLACE NAME WITH "Recovered"
DISPLAY

ECHO --- session ends WITHOUT COMMIT: the .tbj holds a U record, no C marker,
ECHO     and the DBF still says Original. The runner will append a C marker. ---
